<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8"/>
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"/>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="../style.css" type="text/css" media="all"/>
  <title>VIS(1)</title>
</head>
<body>
<table class="head">
  <tr>
    <td class="head-ltitle">VIS(1)</td>
    <td class="head-vol">General Commands Manual</td>
    <td class="head-rtitle">VIS(1)</td>
  </tr>
</table>
<div class="manual-text">
<section class="Sh">
<h1 class="Sh" id="NAME"><a class="permalink" href="#NAME">NAME</a></h1>
<p class="Pp"><code class="Nm">vis</code>, <code class="Nm">unvis</code>
    &#x2014; <span class="Nd">display non-printable characters or decode
    them</span></p>
</section>
<section class="Sh">
<h1 class="Sh" id="SYNOPSIS"><a class="permalink" href="#SYNOPSIS">SYNOPSIS</a></h1>
<table class="Nm">
  <tr>
    <td><code class="Nm">vis</code></td>
    <td>[<var class="Ar">file ...</var>]</td>
  </tr>
</table>
<br/>
<table class="Nm">
  <tr>
    <td><code class="Nm">unvis</code></td>
    <td>[<var class="Ar">file ...</var>]</td>
  </tr>
</table>
</section>
<section class="Sh">
<h1 class="Sh" id="DESCRIPTION"><a class="permalink" href="#DESCRIPTION">DESCRIPTION</a></h1>
<p class="Pp">The <code class="Nm">vis</code> utility reads the given files (or
    standard input if no files are specified) and writes the content to standard
    output, converting non-printable characters into a visible
  representation.</p>
<p class="Pp">The <code class="Nm">unvis</code> utility performs the inverse
    operation, decoding visual representations (like <code class="Li">\n</code>
    or <code class="Li">\001</code>) back into their original raw byte form.</p>
<p class="Pp">Characters are processed as follows in
    <code class="Nm">vis</code>:</p>
<ul class="Bl-bullet Bd-indent">
  <li>Printable ASCII characters are passed through unchanged.</li>
  <li>Common control characters are represented by standard C-style escape
      sequences (e.g., <code class="Li">\n</code> for newline,
      <code class="Li">\r</code> for carriage return, <code class="Li">\t</code>
      for tab).</li>
  <li>The backslash character (<code class="Li">\</code>) is escaped as
      <code class="Li">\\</code>.</li>
  <li>All other non-printable characters are rendered as three-digit octal
      sequences preceded by a backslash (e.g.,
    <code class="Li">\001</code>).</li>
</ul>
</section>
<section class="Sh">
<h1 class="Sh" id="EXIT_STATUS"><a class="permalink" href="#EXIT_STATUS">EXIT
  STATUS</a></h1>
<dl class="Bl-tag">
  <dt>0</dt>
  <dd>Success.</dd>
  <dt>&gt;0</dt>
  <dd>An error occurred (e.g., a file could not be opened).</dd>
</dl>
</section>
<section class="Sh">
<h1 class="Sh" id="EXAMPLES"><a class="permalink" href="#EXAMPLES">EXAMPLES</a></h1>
<p class="Pp">To view hidden characters:</p>
<p class="Pp"></p>
<div class="Bd Bd-indent"><code class="Li">$ vis file.bin</code></div>
<p class="Pp">To restore a file from its visible representation:</p>
<p class="Pp"></p>
<div class="Bd Bd-indent"><code class="Li">$ unvis encoded.txt &gt;
  original.bin</code></div>
</section>
<section class="Sh">
<h1 class="Sh" id="SEE_ALSO"><a class="permalink" href="#SEE_ALSO">SEE
  ALSO</a></h1>
<p class="Pp"><a class="Xr" href="../html1/cat.html">cat(1)</a></p>
</section>
</div>
